The two Population Tables differ in exactly the same way the two Preceptor Tables did: one outcome column versus two, with hatching and ... notation in the causal version to handle the unobservable counterfactual.

5.2.7 Probability family and link function
The probability family is determined by the outcome’s distribution. height is continuous, so the family is Normal:
\[Y \sim \mathcal{N}(\mu, \sigma^2)\]
The link function for a continuous outcome is the identity, so:
\[\mu = \beta_0 + \beta_1 X_1 + \cdots + \beta_n X_n\]
Our model will be a linear regression. The covariates we will use are determined in Courage.

